description:
Age of Bronze is a comics series by writer/artist Eric Shanower retelling the legend of the Trojan War.  The series aims to be true to all literary traditions, from Homer's Iliad to Shakespeare's Troilus and Cressida, as well as to the archaeology  of the Bronze Age Aegean.   It began in 1998 and when complete it is projected to comprise seven volumes.  Shanower aims tp publish 2-3 issues per year.

Shanower won the Eisner Award for best writer/artist in 2001 and 2003, and was nominated for the Ignatz Award for outstanding artist in 1999, for his work on Age of Bronze. The series was also nominated for the R.A.C. &quot;Squiddy&quot; Award for Best Ongoing Comic Series in 1999, 2000, 2001, and 2002.



